snippet.textDisplay:
"Seasonal Flu is still the biggest threat"

Season Flu kills about 0.07% of those it infects, it happens every year, we know what to expect and we can even predict months in advance what strains will be most prominent come the winter. On top of that, there is also a vaccine.

Coronavirus kills about 2% of those it infects. It's just as infectious as seasonal flu but we know very little about it and there's no vaccine.

I'd say that's a much larger threat, even if it's not as widespread yet, it's potential to become widespread makes it a larger threat.
